Another rainfall rendered 126 homeless at Yana village of Kuraye ward in Charanchi Local Government Area of Katsina State yesterday This was coming barely 24 hours after hundreds were rendered homeless in Mashi and Musawa towns of the state. The executive secretary of the state Emergency Management Agency Dr Aminu Waziri confirmed the development. He described the situation as alarming as many families have completely lost their houses and many animals perished following buildings collapse. “In each household you can have between 5 and 6 families with children, this was more devastating because most of the houses were made of mud,” he said He said a team of personnel are on ground distributing food items, clothes to the victims as most of them have lost their food to the rains. He listed the items to include bags each of rice, millet, maize and spaghetti to assists the victims.